Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper describes the design and implementation of a cluster of raspberry pi single board computers and evaluates its performance on computational tasks.
- cs.ED (Education) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of the cluster as an educational tool for classroom usage.
- cs.CE (Computer Engineering) is another possible category as the paper describes the design and configuration of the cluster hardware.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of the cluster for parallel metaheuristics, which may involve programming languages and parallel algorithms.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the resource contention with operating system level processes when attempting to utilize all four cores of all cluster nodes for a parallel computation, which may involve software engineering considerations.
